result.execSummary:
The defendant Ashley M Finzel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Court will allow early termination of probation after 6 months and upon an affirmative recommendation of the probation agent.

records.addlTxt:
10:55 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Jeanne Zamzow.  Lisa Vanden Branden for the State of Wisconsin.  Court recites agreement - defendant will plea to the charge.  State concurs.  Atty Zamzow concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Zamzow.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:  SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 1 year.  Court will allow early termination of probation after 6 months and upon an affirmative recommendation of the probation agent.

CONDITIONS:

court costs
25 hours community service  
Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent

Court adjourned at 11:01 a.m.

1:17 p.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by defendant - will be getting an attorney.  Court will set for status hearing on April 20, 2015 at 1:00 p.m.

Court adjourned at 1:18 p.m.

1:25 p.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by defendant, will be meeting with the PD tomorrow.  Court will set for status hearing on April 6, 2015 at 1:00 p.m.

Court adjourned at 1:26 p.m.
Status hearing on March 16, 2015 at 01:00 pm.

1:35 p.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading.  Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  Court instructs the defendant of his right to an attorney.  Defendant enters a plea of NOT GUILTY.  DA makes bond recommendation.  Court sets bond at $500.00 signature bond.  Court will set for Status Hearing on March 16, 2015 at 1:00 p.m.

Court adjourned at 1:36 p.m.
